  <prompt>
    Filed 2026-05-27 per operator mandate: "this r4 project is a clean up project so we need
    to address this now because it keeps getting lost/overlooked/deferred". Bring the
    @spaarke/ui-components warning count from 161 down to ≤30. Bulk-pattern approach.

    DO NOT mass-silence rules via // eslint-disable comments. DO NOT add // @ts-ignore.
    DO NOT modify code to silence warnings unless the silencing is a legitimate type-correctness
    improvement.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    TypeScript hygiene engineer. Bulk-pattern bias. Skip surgical rewrites — if a warning needs
    more than a small fix, document as carry-over.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `npm run lint` in `@spaarke/ui-components` reports ≤30 warnings (down from 161). 0 errors.
    No `// eslint-disable-next-line` additions. No behavior changes. Remaining warnings
    documented with reason in `notes/078-eslint-sweep.md`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per notes/b9-lint-warnings.md, the 161 warnings break down:
      - 78 `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` — replace `any` with `unknown` and narrow
      - 42 `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` — prefix with `_` or delete dead code
      - 22 `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps` — case-by-case; some are real missing deps
      - 11 unused `eslint-disable` directives — delete the comments
      - 3 `@typescript-eslint/no-require-imports` — replace `require()` with ES imports
      - 2 `@typescript-eslint/no-var-requires` — companion of above
      - 2 `import/first` (directive-only) — resolved by 065 plugin registration
      - 2 `jsx-a11y/...` (directive-only) — resolved by 065 plugin registration
      - 1 `@typescript-eslint/prefer-as-const`
      - 1 `prefer-const`
      - 1 `@typescript-eslint/no-empty-object-type`
      - (10 rules-of-hooks already fixed by task 073)

      Bulk patterns:
      1. Delete unused `eslint-disable` comments — easy, all 11 in one pass
      2. Prefix unused-var args with `_` (existing convention) — ~30 of the 42 should be quick
      3. Replace `any` → `unknown` + add narrowing — careful pass; some `any`s are at SDK boundaries (annotate per the task 067 pattern)
      4. Replace `require()` → ES imports — 5 errors total
      5. Address misc one-offs

      Realistic target: get to ≤30 within 8h budget. Anything more invasive than that becomes
      carry-over (next "type tightening" project).

      DO NOT touch DatasetGrid/GridView.tsx + ListView.tsx beyond what task 073 changed.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/eslint.config.js</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">NO `// eslint-disable-line` or `// eslint-disable-next-line` additions. If a warning genuinely can't be fixed, downgrade the rule's scope (e.g., file-scoped override) or leave it and document as carry-over.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NO `// @ts-ignore` or `// @ts-nocheck` additions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NO behavior change. Type fixes only. If a fix requires behavior change, document as escalation candidate; do NOT make the change without operator approval.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Hard budget cap: 8h. If approaching budget without hitting ≤30 target, STOP and document remaining warnings as carry-overs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">For `any → unknown` conversions: narrow at use site. If narrowing requires substantial logic, leave as `any` and document.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">For `unused-vars`: `_`-prefix unused args (existing convention from b9 memo); delete clearly-dead-code unused locals.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 patterns. For `exhaustive-deps`: don't silence; if the dep is genuinely irrelevant, restructure to remove the dep; else add the dep and verify no infinite loops.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">After sweep: verify `npm test` still passes — type fixes should not break tests.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-react-19-code-pages.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/b9-lint-warnings.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/b11-cast-inventory.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Baseline">Run `npm run lint` in `@spaarke/ui-components`. Capture full warning list. Confirm count is 151 (after 073 removed 10 rules-of-hooks). Group by rule.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Quick wins (Pass 1)">Bulk pass on the lowest-friction patterns:
      - Delete 11 unused `eslint-disable` directives
      - `_`-prefix the unused-args portion of the 42 unused-vars warnings (~30 of 42 likely)
      - Replace 5 `require()` calls with ES imports
      - Fix the 5 misc one-offs (prefer-as-const, prefer-const, no-empty-object-type, jsx-a11y/import directive-only)
      Re-run lint. Expect ~60-80 fewer warnings after this pass.</step>
    <step order="3" name="any → unknown (Pass 2)">Walk the 78 `no-explicit-any` warnings. For each: replace `any` with `unknown` and narrow at use site. Skip if narrowing requires substantial logic — document the skip. Re-run lint after each ~10 fixes to verify no regression.</step>
    <step order="4" name="exhaustive-deps (Pass 3)">Walk the 22 `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps` warnings. For each: read the surrounding code carefully. If dep is genuinely missing, add it; verify no infinite loop. If dep is genuinely irrelevant, restructure to remove the dep (e.g., move logic outside the effect). Skip if restructure is non-trivial — document.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Tally + carry-overs">Re-run lint. If ≤30: SUCCESS. If between 30-60: document remaining + reason; still SUCCESS by acceptance. If >60: STOP and document — flag as carry-over to a follow-up project.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Test verification">`npm test` in `@spaarke/ui-components` — all tests pass.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Build verification">`npm run build` — 0 errors. (If new tsc errors appear from type tightening, address them.)</step>
    <step order="8" name="Document">Write `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/078-eslint-sweep.md` with:
      - Initial vs final warning counts (per rule)
      - Bulk patterns applied
      - Skipped warnings + reasons (carry-overs)
      - Recommendation: which rules can be promoted to `error` in a future pass
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Inspect affected files</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Apply fixes</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">npm run lint, npm test, npm run build</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Find rule occurrences</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
