    <criterion testable="true">Given the change, When `grep -rn "// @ts-ignore\|// @ts-nocheck" src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/` runs, Then no NEW occurrences.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the change, When `npm test` runs in `@spaarke/ui-components`, Then tests pass (≤4 failures from 077 carry-overs is acceptable).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the change, When `npm run build` runs, Then 0 errors.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    This is the "lint warning debt sweep" the operator called out by name. The R4 build-hygiene
    cluster has been deferring this for too long. Hard budget at 8h — if cascade reveals deeper
    issues, that's a separate project.

    Common patterns to expect:
    - Mock files in `__mocks__/` and `__tests__/` are full of `any` casts; these are
      legitimate test-scaffolding. Use a file-scoped override in eslint.config.js if needed
      (already configured per the b9 memo).
    - SDK-boundary `(window as any).Xrm` casts — annotate with `// SDK boundary: Xrm runtime`
      comment (pattern from task 067) and leave the cast.
  </notes>

